HEADWORD: Book muslin
<hw>Book" mus`lin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of muslin
used for the covers of books.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of thin white muslin for ladies'
dresses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bookplate</ent>⟦br⟧
